<br>
What i REALLY detest about certain mobs, is the requirement for camps that exceed 8 consecutive hours...I mean 50+ hours waiting for something to spawn?  COME ON...people need to eat/sleep/work for god's sake!<br>
<br>
I thought of this idea recently:  <br>
<br>
As we know, Epics are pretty much serial quests that can involve 50+ NON-CONSECUTIVE hours ...where piece A drops from a  mob that has a 4 hour spawn...piece B drops from a mob that has an 8 hour spawn...rinse, repeat, all the way to piece Z, if necessary.  No problem.  It's when you throw in one piece like the Heart that someone has to camp non-stop for so long that people really get pissed...<br>
<br>
So, increase Ragefire's spawn rate to every 8-12 hours and then in order to control the number of cleric epics entering the game, just make the loot RARE instead of &quot;always drops&quot;   (example from another Epic quest:  Phinny...spawn time is not hugely unreasonable...doesn't drop the Blue Crystal Staff every time, so if you lose the race to the camp this time, so what?)<br>
<br>
The other idea I had was to make the dragon Ragefire in SF triggerable again, once the human version pops up AND <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> code the HEART as lootable by the cleric who triggered him ONLY - NO EXCEPTIONS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I hope the GM's pay attention to that last one, if it's is do-able, wouldn't it save them time and some major headaches having to listen to all the petitions???  Time better spent on running Events and other duties?<br>
